main event: A civilian observed a UFO with multiple colored lights in the sky over Clyde, New York, on August 20, 1967.
interesting points: The object had 3 or 4 large red lights on the bottom and some amber-colored lights that were not blinking., The observer mentioned that a town policeman saw the object, but later reported he had not seen any UFOs that day., The sighting lasted approximately 2 minutes., The case was concluded with 'Insufficient Clarity' due to the poor quality of the photographs., The observer has had a continuing interest in UFOs and has reported previous sightings.
sighted object: UFO with red and amber lights
witness description: Civilian with a continued interest in UFOs
